Start points are used to ensure an even cutting result throughout the garden.Up to 5 starting points can be setFor each start point, set:Distance - Distance along the wire to the point.How often – Between 0-100%. If 100% the mower always starts from this point. If 50%, half of the time. The sum of all starting points cannot exceed 100%. Whatever the remainder is, the mower will use the default starting point i.e. directly from the charging station.Typically the "How often" should be set to the corresponding area portion that the start point should cover

Setting and choises regarding your installation of the robotic lawn mower.

Disable Follow the boundary wire if the mower will have problem following the boundary wire back to the charging station, ex. If there is a narrow passage to pass on the way. if you choose to disable, you need to have a guide wire installed!
The guide wire is to guide the mower to different areas of your garden and to make it easier for the mower to find the charging station again.

If rain guard is activated, the mower keeps track of the rainfall the latest day. If above the level where water runs the risk of standing in the lawn, the mower will pause in the charging station until enough time has passed so that the water has disappeared.NOTE! This means that the mower still will work if light rain is present, only if heavy rainfall has been present the mower will pause.If not activated, the mower will work according to scheduled times independent of rain.

Start points are used to ensure an even cutting result throughout the garden. Up to 5 starting points can be used.For each starting point, set:Distance - Distance along the wire to the point.How often - Between 0-100%.Route - What wire to follow when the mower exits the charging station.

If the frost guard is activated, the mower will monitor the risk for freezing temperatures. If there is risk for frost, the mower will pause in the charging station. If the frost guard is inactivated, the mower will follow its settings regardless of frost.

Your robotic lawn mower mows in a random pattern starting from the charging station by default. To make sure that you receive an optimal cutting result all over your lawn, you can add starting points. The mower will, at a chosen percentage of the working time, move to and start cutting from the chosen starting point. Up to 5 starting points can be used.

Choose the direction that the mower should follow to reach the starting point. The mower can follow along either the guide wire (guide 1 or 2) or the boundary wire (left or right) from the charging station to reach the starting point.
Choose a distance along either route to create your starting point. The mover will move this chosen distance along the wire in the route direction before starting to cut.

Decide how often the mower should start cutting for each starting point.- 100% - the mower will always start cutting from this point.- 50% - the mower will on average start from this point every second time.- Typically, the "How often" percentage should be the same as the corresponding area\'s size of the garden. It is usually a successful division when a smaller part of the garden that corresponds to 10% of the whole garden area should be set to 10%.
Mowing will start from the charging station this often;

Turn on and off the Power station’s LED and select one of the 4 different light settings (strong, bright, low, or SOS). You can manage this in the app and with the physical button on the Power station.
A short press on the physical button will loop;
1. Low light2. Normal light3. Strong light4. Turn the light off.
A long press on the physical button will:
1. Activate SOS flashing.2. Turn off SOS flashing.
Turn on and off the power output through the DC/USB outlet. The function is synced with the physical button on the Power station.

The USB outlet has an automatic idle mode. When there is no product plugged into the USB outlet or when your product is fully charged, the Power station will turn off the power after the time set in the USB-timer. This is useful to maintain good battery health of the product that is being charged and to save the Power station’s energy.

When charging low-power products (when the current of the USB outlet is lower than 100mA) for instance, a Bluetooth headset or a watch, the idle mode will be activated due to the low energy consumption. This means that the product you are charging will only get power for the amount of time set in the USB-timer. The timer’s default value is 30 seconds, but you can customize the time or disable the USB-timer.
Turn on and off the power output through the AC outlet. The function is synced with the physical button on the Power station.

Turning on the X-Volt function will allow you to exceed the maximum AC output limit by 10%. This makes it possible to power a wider range of products. This function works best for heat equipment (that are not sensitive to low voltages).

Important: Be aware that the X-Volt function is not applicable to all electrical products! Products with strict voltage requirements could potentially take damage. Consult the product\'s manual to see if strict voltage requirements apply to the product you wish to use the X-Volt function for.
